<title>USA: Alliant Foodservice acquires Georgia distributor.</title>
<headline>Alliant Foodservice acquires Georgia distributor.</headline>
<dateline>DEERFIELD, Ill. 1997-01-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Alliant Foodservice Inc, the nation's second largest broadline foodservice distributor, said Friday it acquired Atlanta, Ga.-based Belca Foodservice.</p>
<p>Terms were not disclosed.</p>
<p>Alliant's newest acquisition will have more than 400 employees. Alliant said it intends to invest more than $8 million in capital improvements to its Norcross, Ga., distribution center to accommodate accelerated sales growth in the region.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk 312 408-8787))</p>
